            </rs>. Jos. Torkington deposed, that on Tuesday Night, about Eight o'Clock, the Sash of his Shop Window was lifted up by a Person unknown, and three Wigs taken away. The Prisoner was soon after carry'd before Justice Mitchell for abusing a Constable, when one of those was found in his Pocket, which by Order of the Justice was advertised, and the Prosecutor came and described it. The Prisoner in his Defence said, that he bought the Wig of one 
