                     <interp inst="t17250224-60-person323" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             (a Boy) was then present. John Coomes deposed, that he saw the Prisoner cheapning a Wig of an Irishman, who asked 10s. for it; but said, he would not have sold it at that Price, but that his Wife was Lying-in, and he was hard put to it for Money. The Prisoner asked the Irishman if he came honestly by the Wig, and desired this Evidence to be Witness that he bought it fairly. This he said was on Tuesday Morning; but it appeared that the Prosecutor did not lose his Wigs till that same Tuesday Night. <rs id="t17250224-60-verdict323" type="verdictDescription">
